Q Suppose you have an Entity with Name "Student" and it contain multiple attributes,
out which one is "weight". In StudentRepository, If I will declare method with name
 - "List<Student> findAllOrderByWeightDesc()". What do you think will happen

- It will result in Compilation Error

- It will result in Runtime Error

- It will run successfully but give wrong result

- It will run successfully and give right result

Answer - It will result in Compilation Error



Q How can you define a derived query in Spring Data JPA?

- By annotating a method with @Query

- By creating a method in the repository with a specific naming convention

- By using the @DerivedQuery annotation

- By creating an XML configuration

Answer - By creating a method in the repository with a specific naming convention

